quran[15]{c,v,t}:
  19,96,"Indeed those who believed and did good deeds – the Most Gracious will appoint love for them. (In the hearts of other believers.)"
  19,97,"We have therefore made this Qur’an easy upon your tongue, (O dear Prophet Mohammed – peace and blessings be upon him) for you to announce glad tidings with it to those who fear, and warn those who are quarrelsome."
  19,98,"And many a generation We did destroy before them; do you see any one of them or hear their faintest sound?"
  20,1,"Ta-Ha.* (O dear Prophet Mohammed – peace and blessings be upon him) (Alphabets of the Arabic language – Allah and to whomever He reveals know their precise meanings.)"
  20,2,"We have not sent down this Qur’an upon you (O dear Prophet Mohammed – peace and blessings be upon him) for you to fall into hardship! (Either because he used to pray at length during the night or because he was distressed due to the disbelievers not accepting faith.)"
  20,3,"Except as a reminder for one who fears."
  20,4,"Sent down by One Who created the earth and the lofty heavens."
  20,5,"The Most Gracious Who, befitting His Majesty, took to the Throne (of control)."
  20,6,"To Him only belongs all whatever is in the heavens and all whatever is in the earth, and all whatever is between them, and all whatever is beneath this wet soil."
  20,7,"And if you speak aloud – so He surely knows the secret and that which is more concealed."
  20,8,"Allah – there is no worship except for Him; His only are the best names."
  20,9,"And did the news of Moosa reach you?"
  20,10,"When he saw a fire and said to his wife, “Wait – I have seen a fire – perhaps I may bring you an ember from it or find a way upon the fire.”"
  20,11,"So when he came near the fire, it was announced, “O Moosa!”"
  20,12,"“Indeed I am your Lord, therefore take off your shoes; indeed you are in the holy valley of Tuwa!”"
